
                             muse.c
                <a simple image color manipulator>

features:
• multiple dithering algorithms
• external palette support
• lightweight and fast

using catppuccin.txt
• before >> https://i.imgur.com/fkzmPtQ.jpg
• after  >> https://i.imgur.com/tkTjHtR.png

see ./makefile for a easy installation

§ installation
git clone https://github.com/getjared/muse.git
cd muse
make
sudo make install

§ dependencies
• c compiler (gcc or clang)
• make
• stb_image.h         (included)
• stb_image_write.h   (included)

§ quick-start
basic usage:
./muse input.jpg output.png catppuccin.txt         : convert with floyd-steinberg (default)
./muse input.jpg output.png nord.txt bayer         : convert using bayer dithering
./muse input.jpg output.png spooky-13.txt ordered  : convert using ordered dithering
./muse input.jpg output.png croma16.txt nodither   : convert without dithering

with blur:
./muse -b 3 input.jpg output.png nord.txt bayer    : convert using blur & strength >>

with super8: (8mm camera)
./muse -s 3 input.png output.png croma16.txt nodither  : convert using super8
./muse -b 1 -s 4 input.jpg output.png nord.txt bayer   : convert using blur & super8

with super panavision 70:
./muse -p 2 input.png output.png nord.txt                  : convert using super panavision
./muse -b 3 -s 2 -p 4 input.png output.png spooky-13.txt   : convert using blur, super8 & super panavision

with direct modification:
• -B (brightness)
• -C (contrast)
• -S (saturation)
  usage examples:
  ./muse -b 3 -s 2 -p 4 -B 10.0 -C 1.2 -S 1.1 input.png output.png nord.txt floyd
  ./muse --blur 5 --super8 3 --panavision 4 --brightness 10.0 --contrast 1.2 --saturation 1.1 input.png output.png nord.txt ordered


dithering methods:
• floyd             : floyd-steinberg dithering (default)
• bayer             : bayer matrix dithering
• ordered           : ordered dithering
• nodither          : no dithering
• blur              : blur effect
• super 8           : 8mm camera effect
• super panavision  : super panavision 70 effect

palettes:
palettes are stored in /usr/local/share/muse/palettes after installation
custom palettes can be added by copying .txt files to this directory
palette format is compatible with lospec palette files (PAINT.NET txt file)

§ credits
